President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring October 2012 as National Disability Employment Awareness Month. In the proclamation, President Obama highlights the progress made in the 22 years since the Americans with Disabilities Act was signed, but acknowledges that people with disabilities still face challenges in the workplace. The President emphasizes the importance of giving everyone the opportunity to participate fully in the workforce and calls for a diverse workforce that includes people with disabilities. He notes that the Federal Government is working to increase recruitment, hiring, and retention of people with disabilities and improve compliance with accessibility laws. The proclamation urges all Americans to embrace the talents and skills of individuals with disabilities and promote equal employment opportunities for all.